### HMS — Gateway API Collection
### All requests go through the gateway (port 3000).
### The gateway validates the JWT, enforces RBAC, and injects X-User-* headers.
### Run setup-keycloak.sh before using this file.

@gatewayUrl  = http://localhost:3000
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8080

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 0. LOGIN — get tokens for each role
#    Keycloak endpoint (call directly, NOT through gateway)
#    Seed accounts created by scripts/setup-keycloak.sh  password: Password@123
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 0a. Login as admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=admin&password=Password%40123

###
@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.access_token}}

### 0b. Login as doctor (dr.smith)
# @name loginDoctor
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=dr.smith&password=Password%40123

###
@doctorToken = {{loginDoctor.response.body.access_token}}

### 0c. Login as nurse (nurse.silva)
# @name loginNurse
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=nurse.silva&password=Password%40123

###
@nurseToken = {{loginNurse.response.body.access_token}}

### 0d. Login as receptionist
# @name loginReceptionist
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=reception1&password=Password%40123

###
@receptionistToken = {{loginReceptionist.response.body.access_token}}

### 0e. Login as lab technician
# @name loginLabTech
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=labtech1&password=Password%40123

###
@labTechToken = {{loginLabTech.response.body.access_token}}

### 0f. Login as ward staff
# @name loginWardStaff
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/hms/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id=hms-client&username=ward.staff1&password=Password%40123

###
@wardStaffToken = {{loginWardStaff.response.body.access_token}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GATEWAY HEALTH & AUTH TESTS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Health check — no token required
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/health

###

### Expect 401 — no token on protected route
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

###

### Expect 403 — lab_tech cannot access /patients
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ADMIN — RBAC ROUTE RULES  (admin JWT required for all)
# Manage route-to-role access at runtime — no restart needed.
# Rules are matched top-to-bottom; first match wins.
# GET /admin/routes first to find the index before using PUT or DELETE.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### A1. List all rules (with indices)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### A2. Add a new rule at position 0 (most specific first)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pattern": "/reports/**",
  "allowedRoles": ["admin", "doctor"],
  "position": 0
}

###

### A3. Add a rule at the end (omit position or use -1)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pattern": "/new-service/**",
  "allowedRoles": ["admin", "nurse", "doctor"]
}

###

### A4. Update roles for rule at index 0
#     Run A1 first to confirm the index of the rule you want to change
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes/0
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allowedRoles": ["admin", "doctor", "nurse", "receptionist"]
}

###

### A5. Delete rule at index 0
#     Run A1 first to confirm the index
DELETE {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes/0
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### A6. Restore all 22 built-in default rules (overwrites any custom changes)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes/reset
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### A7. Reload rules from Redis into memory
#     Use this if rules were modified by another gateway instance
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes/reload
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### A8. Expect 401 — no token on admin route
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes

###

### A9. Expect 403 — doctor cannot access admin routes
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/admin/routes
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

###

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# RECEPTION SERVICE  (port 3001 via gateway)
# Roles allowed: admin, receptionist, doctor, nurse (patients/queue/appointments)
#                admin, receptionist (tokens)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### R1. Register a new patient
# @name registerPatient
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Amanda",
  "lastName": "Silva",
  "mobile": "+94711234567",
  "dateOfBirth": "1992-05-15",
  "gender": "female"
}

###
@patientId = {{registerPatient.response.body.data.id}}

### R2. Get patient by ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### R3. Search patients
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/search?q=Amanda
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### R4. Update patient
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Amanda",
  "lastName": "Perera",
  "mobile": "+94711234567",
  "dateOfBirth": "1992-05-15",
  "gender": "female"
}

###

### R5. Issue OPD token
# @name issueToken
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/tokens
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patientId}}",
  "queueType": "opd"
}

###
@tokenId = {{issueToken.response.body.data.id}}

### R6. Get today's tokens
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/tokens/today
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}

###

### R7. Get live OPD queue
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/queue/opd
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### R8. Call token (update status)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/tokens/{{tokenId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "called"
}

###

### R9. Book appointment
# @name bookAppointment
# Replace doctorId with a real UUID from staff-service after creating a doctor
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/appointments
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patientId}}",
  "doctorId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "appointmentDate": "2026-04-01",
  "fromTime": "09:00",
  "toTime": "09:15"
}

###
@appointmentId = {{bookAppointment.response.body.data.id}}

### R10. List appointments for a date
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/appointments?date=2026-04-01
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}

###

### R11. Cancel appointment
DELETE {{gatewayUrl}}/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{receptionistToken}}

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STAFF SERVICE  (port 3003 via gateway)
# Roles allowed: admin only for all /doctors, /departments, /schedules, /staff
#                admin + nurse for /nurse-allocations
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S1. List departments
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/departments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### S2. Create department
# @name createDept
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/departments
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "General Physician",
  "description": "Primary care and general medicine"
}

###
@deptId = {{createDept.response.body.data.id}}

### S3. Create doctor (multipart — use curl for file upload, JSON-only example here)
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/doctors \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <adminToken>" \
#   -F "first_name=Jenny" -F "last_name=Smith" \
#   -F "username=dr.jennysmith" -F "email=jenny.smith@hospital.com" \
#   -F "mobile=+94771234567" -F "password=Password@123" \
#   -F "date_of_birth=1985-05-20" -F "gender=female" \
#   -F "education=MBBS, MS" -F "designation=Senior Physician" \
#   -F "department_id=DEPT_ID_HERE"

###

### S4. List all doctors
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/doctors
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### S5. List doctors by department
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/doctors?department_id={{deptId}}&status=active
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### S6. Create staff member (nurse)
# @name createNurse
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/staff
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Sarah Williams",
  "role": "nurse",
  "email": "sarah.williams@hospital.com",
  "mobile": "+94779876543"
}

###
@nurseStaffId = {{createNurse.response.body.data.id}}

### S7. List available nurses for a date
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/staff/available?date=2026-04-10&role=nurse
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### S8. List all staff
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/staff
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# Replace with real doctor UUID and nurse UUID after creating them
### S9. Allocate nurse to doctor session
# @name allocateNurse
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/nurse-allocations
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nurse_id": "{{nurseStaffId}}",
  "doctor_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "session_date": "2026-04-10"
}

###
@allocationId = {{allocateNurse.response.body.data.id}}

### S10. Complete allocation
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/nurse-allocations/{{allocationId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CLINICAL SERVICE  (port 3002 via gateway)
# Roles: admin, doctor, nurse
# Gateway injects X-User-Id (Keycloak UUID) and X-User-Name from the JWT
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### C1. Create clinical session
# @name createSession
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patientId}}",
  "sessionType": "opd",
  "chiefComplaint": "Persistent fever for 3 days"
}

###
@sessionId = {{createSession.response.body.data.id}}

### C2. List sessions
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

###

### C3. Get session by ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

###

### C4. Record vitals
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/vitals
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bpm": 88,
  "temperature": 38.2,
  "bloodPressureSys": 118,
  "bloodPressureDia": 76,
  "spo2": 97,
  "weightKg": 65.0,
  "heightCm": 168
}

###

### C5. Add prescriptions
# @name addPrescriptions
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prescriptions": [
    {
      "type": "internal",
      "medicineName": "Paracetamol",
      "dosage": "500mg",
      "frequency": "Every 8 hours",
      "durationDays": 5,
      "instructions": "Take after meals"
    },
    {
      "type": "external",
      "medicineName": "Amoxicillin",
      "dosage": "500mg",
      "frequency": "Three times daily",
      "durationDays": 7,
      "pharmacyName": "City Pharmacy"
    }
  ]
}

###

### C6. Request lab tests
# Replace testId values with real UUIDs from lab-service after creating tests
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/lab-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tests": [
    { "testId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001", "urgency": "routine" }
  ],
  "notes": "Suspected typhoid — check Widal"
}

###

### C7. Complete session (triggers billing.opd + pharmacy.new_rx NATS events)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "diagnosis": "Typhoid Fever — Widal test positive",
  "discountPercent": 0
}

###

### C8. Get patient clinical history
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}/history?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{doctorToken}}

###

### C9. Get pharmacy queue (completed sessions with pending internal prescriptions)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/pharmacy/queue
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### C10. Dispense prescription — replace rxId with a real UUID from C9
@rxId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/pharmacy/{{rxId}}/dispense
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LAB SERVICE  (port 3005 via gateway)
# Roles: admin, lab_tech (tests + orders)
#        admin, lab_tech, doctor (orders)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### L1. Add test to catalog — Complete Blood Count
# @name addTestCBC
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/tests
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Complete Blood Count",
  "code": "CBC",
  "category": "Haematology",
  "unitPrice": 750.00,
  "turnaroundHours": 4,
  "referenceRange": "WBC: 4.5-11.0 x10³/μL, RBC: 4.5-5.5 x10⁶/μL"
}

###
@cbcTestId = {{addTestCBC.response.body.data.id}}

### L2. Add test — Widal
# @name addTestWidal
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/tests
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Widal Test",
  "code": "WIDAL",
  "category": "Microbiology",
  "unitPrice": 500.00,
  "turnaroundHours": 24,
  "referenceRange": "Negative < 1:80 titre"
}

###
@widalTestId = {{addTestWidal.response.body.data.id}}

### L3. Get test catalog
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/tests
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}

###

### L4. Register walk-in lab order
# @name createOrder
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientName": "Andrea Lalema",
  "patientMobile": "+94771234567",
  "source": "walk_in",
  "tests": [
    { "testId": "{{cbcTestId}}", "urgency": "routine" },
    { "testId": "{{widalTestId}}", "urgency": "urgent" }
  ],
  "notes": "Patient reports fever for 4 days"
}

###
@orderId = {{createOrder.response.body.data.id}}
@orderTestId1 = {{createOrder.response.body.data.tests[0].id}}
@orderTestId2 = {{createOrder.response.body.data.tests[1].id}}

### L5. List orders
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}

###

### L6. Get order by ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}

###

### L7. Enter results — first test (status → processing)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/results
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "results": [
    {
      "orderTestId": "{{orderTestId1}}",
      "resultValue": "WBC: 9.2 x10³/μL — all values normal",
      "isAbnormal": false,
      "technicianNotes": "Within normal range"
    }
  ]
}

###

### L8. Enter results — second test (status → completed)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/results
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "results": [
    {
      "orderTestId": "{{orderTestId2}}",
      "resultValue": "S.Typhi O: 1:160 — significant titre",
      "isAbnormal": true,
      "technicianNotes": "Recommend clinical correlation"
    }
  ]
}

###

### L9. Record payment (triggers billing.lab NATS event to finance)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}/pay
Authorization: Bearer {{labTechToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentMethod": "cash",
  "amountPaid": 1250.00
}

###

### L10. Upload report PDF — use curl for multipart:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/orders/ORDER_ID/report \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer LAB_TOKEN" \
#   -F "report=@/path/to/report.pdf;type=application/pdf" \
#   -F "notes=Typhoid confirmed"

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WARD SERVICE  (port 3006 via gateway)
# Roles: admin, ward_staff (wards/beds/admissions)
#        admin, ward_staff, doctor, nurse (admissions)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### W1. Create Male General Ward (auto-generates beds)
# @name createWard
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Male General Ward",
  "type": "general",
  "capacity": 20
}

###
@wardId = {{createWard.response.body.data.id}}

### W2. Create ICU
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ICU",
  "type": "icu",
  "capacity": 6
}

###

### W3. List all wards (with occupancy)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{wardStaffToken}}

###

### W4. List available beds in ward
# @name listAvailableBeds
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/beds?ward_id={{wardId}}&status=available
Authorization: Bearer {{wardStaffToken}}

###

### W5. Admit patient
# @name admitPatient
# Update bedId from W4 response
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{wardStaffToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "{{patientId}}",
  "patientName": "Amanda Perera",
  "patientNumber": "R00001",
  "bedId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "attendingDoctorId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "attendingDoctorName": "Dr. Jenny Smith",
  "admissionReason": "High fever — IV treatment required",
  "notes": "No known allergies"
}

###
@admissionId = {{admitPatient.response.body.data.id}}

### W6. List current admissions
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions?status=admitted
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### W7. Add bed charge
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions/{{admissionId}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{wardStaffToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceName": "Daily Bed Charge",
  "serviceType": "bed_charge",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 2500.00,
  "notes": "Day 1"
}

###

### W8. Add medication charge
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions/{{admissionId}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceName": "IV Ceftriaxone 1g",
  "serviceType": "medication",
  "quantity": 2,
  "unitPrice": 450.00
}

###

### W9. Get admission with running total
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions/{{admissionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### W10. Discharge patient (triggers billing.ward NATS event to finance)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/admissions/{{admissionId}}/discharge
Authorization: Bearer {{wardStaffToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dischargeNotes": "Patient recovered. Discharged with oral antibiotics.",
  "dischargeDiagnosis": "Typhoid Fever — resolved"
}

###

### W11. Patient admission history
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
